-- Siemens’s Nokia Deal Said to Boost Profit by 300 Million Euros
-- B y   A l e x   W e b b
-- 2013-07-25T12:09:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-25/siemens-s-nokia-deal-said-to-boost-profit-by-300-million-euros.html
Siemens AG (SIE) ’s earnings this year will
be boosted by about 300 million euros ($395 million) from
selling a stake in Nokia Siemens Networks, people familiar with
the matter said.  Siemens, which announced the 1.7 billion-euro sale of 50
percent in the phone-equipment venture to  Nokia Oyj (NOK1V)  this month,
will include gains from the deal in its net income from
continuing operations, the people said, asking not to be
identified as the matter is not public.  Siemens is scheduled to report fiscal third-quarter
earnings on Aug. 1.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Simon Thiel in London at 
